    <note>Shi(5) Rong [18134] Davis' genealogical tables have his mingzi as Hong, butI follow Ye(1) Shi's funerary inscription for Shi(5) Jian(2) [10382], which records his mingzi as Rong. Davis identifies his adopted heir, Migong [18137], as the second rather than fourth son of Jian(2) for reasons that are neither given nor clear either from Ye(1) Shi's funerary inscription or the genealogical tables; the former makes him the 4th son, the latter, the 7th son. I keep as 4th son. I am treating Migong and his descendants as members of jia 'e' of this lineage. Davis, p. 158.</note>
